show.description: When their worlds collide, Mia and James strike an unusual deal—a marriage of convenience that promises to solve both their problems. On paper, it's strictly business. In reality, it's anything but simple. As they craft the perfect façade of marital bliss, these two strangers find themselves navigating awkward dinners, stolen glances, and the delicate art of keeping up appearances. What begins as a calculated arrangement slowly transforms into something neither expected. In this charming romantic comedy, discover how pretending to be in love might just be the perfect recipe for finding the real thing.
